Parliament, Sunday 16 May 2021 –The National Assembly (NA) will hold nine (9) virtual Mini Plenaries dealing with 19 Budget Votes and, the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) will cover Policy Debates on three (3) Budget Votes at its plenary sittings this week.
	
	The NCOP virtual plenary sitting on Tuesday, starting at 10:00, is scheduled to have Policy Debates on Vote 3: Co-operative Governance and Traditional Affairs and Vote 29: Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development.
	
	On Thursday, the NCOP is scheduled to have a Policy Debate on Budget Vote 34: Mineral Resources and Energy at its plenary sitting at 14:00.
	
	Meanwhile, on Tuesday, the National Assembly’s three mini plenaries will cover eight (8) Budget Votes and these are - Vote 38: Tourism; Vote 39: Trade, Industry and Competition; Vote 34: Mineral Resources and Energy; Vote 33: Human Settlements; Vote 23 & 26: Defence and Military Veterans; Vote 27: Office of the Chief Justice; Vote 30: Communications and Digital Technologies and Vote 35: Science and Innovation.
	
	On Wednesday, two mini-plenaries will be held and will feature the Department of Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation; Women and Home Affairs.
	
	Thursday’s five Budget Votes will include Vote 22: Correctional Services; Vote 28, 24 & 21: Police (including Independent Police Investigative Directorate and Civilian Secretariat for the Police Service); Vote 6: International Relations and Cooperation; Vote 11, 7 & 12: Public Service and Administration (National School of Government and Public Service Commission); Vote 16: Basic Education and Vote 8: National Treasury.
	
	Friday’s mini-plenary will deal with Vote 40: Transport and Vote 4: Government Communications and Information System.
	
	At least 30 committee meetings of both houses are scheduled this week including, the Public Hearings on Expropriation by Portfolio Committee on Public Works and Infrastructure. The Expropriation Public Hearings will take place in Kwa-Zulu Natal from Thursday to Sunday.
	
	Committee meetings and activities scheduled for the week ahead include:
	
	TUESDAY, 19 MAY
	Standing Committee on Appropriations: Briefing by the Department of Social Development on the Appropriation Bill
	
	Standing Committee on Finance: Public Hearings on the Financial Sector Laws Amendment Bill
	
	Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs: Briefing by the Electoral Commission of South Africa (IEC) on the annual report and financial statements for 2019-2020; Consideration and adoption of the Budget vote report of the Department of Home Affairs and entities
	
	Select Committee on Finance: Briefing by IRBA on: Implications of changes in IRBA over the past 6 months; On implementation of the amendments to the Act; On their last quarterly report
	
	Select Committee on Land Reform, Environment, Mineral Resources and Energy, Negotiating Mandate Meeting on the National Forest Amendment Bill
	
	Select Committee on Trade and Industry, Economic Development, Small Business Development, Tourism, Employment and Labour: Briefing on Budget Vote and Annual Performance Plan of the Department of Small Business Development
	
	Portfolio Committee on Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development: Consideration of the input from the National House of Traditional Leaders (NHTL) on the Liquor Products Amendment Bill
	
	Portfolio Committee on Health: Public hearings on the National Health Insurance (NHI) Bill
	
	Portfolio Committee on Basic Education: Consideration and Adoption of Committee Report on Budget Vote: Basic Education; Follow-up on Oversight Recommendations agreed to for E T Thabane Full Service School, Mount Fletcher by: Eastern Cape Department of Education; and Department of Basic Education
	
	Standing Committee on Public Accounts: Hearing on the annual report and financial statements of the National Skills Fund (NSF), for the financial year 2019/20, as well as irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure
	
	Standing Committee on Public Accounts: Hearing on the annual report and financial statements of the State Information Technology Agency (SITA), for the financial year 2019/20, as well as irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure
	
	Portfolio Committee on Environment, Forestry and Fisheries: Adoption of minutes of the previous minutes; and Briefing by ESKOM on their non-compliance with environmental laws
	
	WEDNESDAY, 20 MAY
	Standing Committee on Finance: Public Hearings on the Pension Funds Amendment Bill.
	
	Standing Committee on Appropriations: Briefing by the Department of Health and the Department of Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development on the Appropriation Bill
	
	Select Committee on Petitions and Executive Undertakings: Overseeing and scrutinising the implementation of the executive undertakings made by the Minister of Small Business Development
	
	Select Committee on Appropriations: Consideration of Negotiating Mandates on the Division of Revenue Bill.
	
	Select Committee on Security and Justice: Briefing by the South African Police Service on the budget and the Annual Performance Plan.
	
	Portfolio Committee on Health, Public hearings on the National Health Insurance (NHI) Bill
	
	Standing Committee on Public Accounts: Hearing on the annual report and financial statements of the Compensation Fund (CF), for the financial year 2019/20, as well as irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure
	
	Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises: Consideration and adoption of budget vote report; Consideration and adoption of Alexkor oversight report
	
	Select Committee on Public Enterprises and Communications: Briefing by the Department of Communication and Digital Technologies on its Strategic Plan and Annual Performance Plan
	
	Portfolio Committee on Defence and Military Veterans: Briefing by DMV on progress regarding amendments to the Military Veterans Act and Military Veterans Benefit Regulations; Briefing by SITA on its support to DMV in its efforts to cleanse the National Military Veterans’ Database.
	
	Select Committee on Transport, Public Service and Administration, Public Works and Infrastructure: Briefing by the Department of Transport on its Annual Performance Plan and Strategic Plan
	
	Select Committee on Education and Technology, Sport, Arts and Culture: Consideration and adoption of Draft Minutes; Briefing by the Department of Science and Innovation on the 2021 Annual Performance Plan and Budget Vote
	
	THURSDAY, 21 MAY
	Portfolio Committee on Health: Public hearings on the National Health Insurance (NHI) Bill
	
	FRIDAY, 22 MAY
	Select Committee on Security and Justice: Briefing by the Civilian Secretariat Police Service on the budget and the Annual Performance Plan (APP) for 2021-2022
	
	Portfolio Committee on Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation: Consideration and adoption of the Report of the PC on the Budget Vote 41, revised APP and Strategic Plan of the Department of Water and Sanitation and Entities, 2021/2
	
	Joint Standing Committee on the Financial Management of Parliament: Briefing by the Executive Authority and the Minister of Finance on progress made as far as addressing concerns about the allocation of Parliament’s budget (including a briefing by the Chairperson of the Parmed Board on progress made in resolving the issues around the Parmed liability)
	
